diff -Naru ACE_wrappers.orig/TAO/tests/RTCORBA/Collocation_AOM_Entry_Refcount/README ACE_wrappers/TAO/tests/RTCORBA/Collocation_AOM_Entry_Refcount/README
--- ACE_wrappers.orig/TAO/tests/RTCORBA/Collocation_AOM_Entry_Refcount/README	1969-12-31 16:00:00.000000000 -0800
+++ ACE_wrappers/TAO/tests/RTCORBA/Collocation_AOM_Entry_Refcount/README	2005-12-07 09:41:07.000000000 -0800
@@ -0,0 +1,24 @@
+$Id$
+
+Description:
+
+This is a test for the reference counting on active object map entries
+when RT collocation is used. This test is a regression for a bug in 
+which the ref count did not get decremented in the following case:
+
+- There are two objects, SourceObj and DestObj, in the same lane of a 
+  thread pool with lanes using a SERVER_DECLARED priority model.
+- SourceObj receives a CORBA call and during the upcall makes a call
+  to DestObj.
+
+The bug consisted of the ref count being incremented in the processing
+of Root_POA::locate_servant_i() and not being decremented when the 
+TAO::Portable_Server::Servant_Upcall object instantiated in 
+TAO_RT_Collocation_Resolver::is_collocated() is destroyed. 
+
+This test goes through this same call chain, checking the ref count in
+the active object map entry (via a special debugging interface added to 
+the AOM that allows it to be queried) at various stages. When the bug does 
+not exist, the ref count should return to 1 when all upcalls are complete. 
+If the ref count is not of the expected value, the test is considered a 
+failure. Without the ref count fix, the ref counts hit grow to about 10.
